HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 331
BY REPRESENTATIVE TAYLOR
COMMENDATIONS: Commends Sheriff Michael Tregre of St. John Parish on his
professional and civic accomplishments
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Sheriff Michael Tregre of St. John Parish on his professional and civic
3 accomplishments.
4 WHEREAS, Sheriff Michael Tregre was born and raised on East 29th Street in
5 Reserve, Louisiana, attended St. Peter Elementary School, and is a 1985 graduate of East
6 St. John High School; and
7 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre began his law enforcement career as a jailor with the
8 St. John Sheriff's Office (SJSO) on February 1, 1988; he took on a patrolman role in 1990
9 and also worked as an uncover narcotics officer; and
10 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre was promoted to detective and earned the rank of
11 sergeant in February 1991; he was promoted to lieutenant on July 1, 1996, and became the
12 first-ever director of internal management for the SJSO; he then took on the role of serving
13 as a public information officer, which earned him the title of spokesperson for the office; and
14 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre was promoted to the rank of captain on August 17, 1999;
15 he applied to the FBI National Academy in Quantico, Virginia, in 2004, and was accepted
16 to the Two Hundred Nineteenth Session of the academy in the fall of that year; he graduated
17 in December 2004 and was promoted to the rank of major by the SJSO on December 17,
18 2004; and
19 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre was elected Sheriff of St. John Parish by sixty-three
20 percent of voters and was sworn in on July 1, 2012; he has been reelected over three
21 consecutive elections and began his fourth term on July 1, 2024; and
