1 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre has provided St. John Parish with a state-of-the-art law
2 enforcement training center that is named in honor of former Sheriff Lloyd B. Johnson; the
3 facility has been used to train parish law enforcement officers as well as officers from
4 around the country and serves as a meeting place for community-based events; and
5 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre partnered with the St. John Parish government to create
6 the Westbank Substation, which houses numerous SJSO employees and serves as a meeting
7 place for the Westbank community; and
8 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre has numerous professional and civic affiliations,
9 including membership in the Louisiana Sheriff's Association, National Sheriff's Association,
10 International Association of Chiefs of Police, Rotary Club of LaPlace, LaPlace Lions Club,
11 and St. Joan of Arc Church; he is a former board member for the St. John Parish American
12 Heart Association and a former board member and past president of both St. John Parish
13 Recreation and St. John Parish Community Action; he is a part of the St. John Parish
14 Emergency Operations Disaster Drill Team and a past president of the St. John Parish
15 Sheriff's Office Crime Fighters Organization; and
16 WHEREAS, Sheriff Tregre is a 1990 graduate of the LSU Basic Police Academy
17 P.O.S.T. and a 2012 graduate of the LA Sheriff's Training Institute, and he completed United
18 States Dignitary Protection Service Training in 2015; he was recognized as the Rotarian of
19 the Month by the Rotary Club of LaPlace in July 2010, he is a 2012 Paul Harris Fellow
20 recipient, and he received the 2024 Crimestoppers of Greater New Orleans Sheriff Harry Lee
21 Lifetime Achievement in Criminal Justice Award; and
22 WHEREAS, Sheriff Michael Tregre is most deserving of recognition for his
23 outstanding dedication to law enforcement and to the protection of the citizens of St. John
24 Parish.
25 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
26 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Sheriff Michael Tregre on his professional
27 and civic accomplishments and does hereby express enduring appreciation for his
28 exceptional service to the citizens of St. John Parish and the state of Louisiana.
